PREAMBLE

This software was created by a single person to solve a real problem:
the internet is not the same everywhere, and when infrastructure fails,
people lose the ability to communicate.

This license protects the work while keeping it free for individuals,
researchers, and humanitarian organizations. It prevents commercial
exploitation without contribution, and protects the identity of the
official network.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

1. DEFINITIONS

"Software" means the Ask Through You source code, documentation,
and all associated files in this repository.

"Author" means Giovanni Nardacci, the original creator.

"You" means any individual or organization using, copying, modifying,
or distributing this Software.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software, or a derivative of it,
primarily intended for commercial advantage or monetary compensation.
This includes selling access, offering paid services, embedding in a
commercial product, or using the Software to generate revenue directly
or indirectly.

"Official Network" means the Ask Through You peer network whose
registry is anchored in the official smart contract on Ethereum,
as published by the Author.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

2. FREE USE

You are free to:

a) Run this Software on any personal device for personal use.

b) Study, learn from, and modify it for personal use.

c) Share unmodified copies of this Software, provided this license
   is included in full.

d) Run a bootstrap server for the official Ask Through You network,
   contributing to the community.

e) Use this Software in academic research, provided the Author is
   credited in any publication.

f) Use this Software in humanitarian operations — including disaster
   response, conflict zones, and civilian protection scenarios —
   at no cost, provided that:

   1. Any public communication, report, or deployment documentation
      acknowledges Human Flag (https://humanflag.org) as the
      originating humanitarian project.

   2. The user accepts and commits to uphold the values of Human Flag:
      the protection of civilians from autonomous weapons systems,
      the promotion of visual surrender protocols, and the facilitation
      of safe surrender and communication between civilians and armed
      actors in conflict zones.

   3. The user agrees to actively support, and not obstruct, the
      ability of civilians to signal surrender and non-combatant
      status, consistent with international humanitarian law.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

3. WHAT REQUIRES WRITTEN PERMISSION

The following uses require explicit written authorization from the Author:

a) Any Commercial Use of the Software or a derivative of it.

b) Embedding this Software, or any substantial portion of it, into
   a product or service distributed to third parties.

c) Creating a competing network that uses this Software's protocol
   or code and presents itself as an alternative to the Official Network.

d) Removing or replacing the Author's attribution in any public-facing
   version of the Software.

To request authorization, contact the Author via the official repository.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

4. ATTRIBUTION — ALWAYS REQUIRED

Any distribution of this Software, modified or unmodified, must:

a) Retain this license file in full.

b) Clearly state the original Author's name: Giovanni Nardacci (nardaxxx).

c) Link to the original repository:
   https://github.com/nardaxxx/askthroughyou

d) If the Software is modified, clearly state what was changed and
   that it is a derivative of the original work.

Removing, hiding, or obscuring attribution is not permitted under
any circumstance.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

5. THE OFFICIAL NETWORK

The Official Network is identified by its Ethereum smart contract
registry, to be published by the Author.

You may not claim that a network you operate is the Official Network,
or operate a registry that impersonates the Official Network.

The protocol is open. The network is one.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

6. CONTRIBUTIONS

If you submit contributions to this repository, you agree that:

a) Your contribution is your original work.

b) The Author may include it in the Software under this license.

c) You retain copyright to your contribution, but grant the Author
   a perpetual, irrevocable license to use it.

